title: Shanklys Best of 2007 July
description:
Only got back a few days ago to sort out Shankly&#039;s Best from July but found enough for three cracking CDs worth of stuff. Highlights include breaking bands, Lodger, Sleeping States, Get Him Eat HIm and Brinkman; old favourites, Gary Numan, the Fiery Furnaces, Super Furry Animals and the Happy Mondays; new remixes of Bloc Party (again) and BRMC; and live tracks from Emma Pollock, Low and a couple from Glastonbury - not to mention a 15 minute track from Gorky&#039;s man Euros Childs. All in all, it should keep you busy through August. TGIS.
